The business community in Mombasa is up in arms against KRA for redeploying a staffer under investigation over graft claims. An internal memo indicates that Nicky Otieno, who was arrested by anti-corruption officers in December for allegedly soliciting a Sh800,000 bribe, will be redeployed from the Trade Facilitation Unit to the Pre-Verification Office at Forodha House.The memo was issued by regional coordinator Southern region Nicholas Kinoti on March 27 this year.Â  Kinoti told the Star the matter has not been prosecuted and the EACC is still investigating. Read: Mombasa KRA official arrested over claims of bribery to release container  Click here for the latest political news